JSE Raises CEO Loubser’s Pay 14%, Newton-King Gets 17% More

-- B y   S i k o n a t h i   M a n t s h a n t s h a
-- 
2011-04-07T15:38:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-07/jse-raises-ceo-loubser-s-pay-14-newton-king-gets-17-more.html
JSE Ltd. (JSE) , a South African company
that operates  Africa ’s biggest stock exchange, paid outgoing
Chief Executive Officer Russell Loubser 14 percent more in 2010
than a year earlier.  Loubser, who steps down at the end of the year, was paid
14.4 million rand ($2.2 million rand) in the year through
December, compared to 12.5 million rand a year earlier, the
Johannesburg-based company said in its  annual report , e-mailed
to shareholders on April 5.  The package includes a “discretionary bonus” of 3.5
million rand, a “special bonus” of 2 million rand and 5.3
million rand in payment for vested performance incentive shares.  Deputy Chief Executive Officer Nicky Newton-King, who will
succeed Loubser, was paid 17 percent more than in 2009. Her 7.2
million rand total package included a “special bonus” of 1.3
million rand and a “discretionary bonus” of 636,000 rand while
vested performance incentive shares delivered another 3.2
million rand.  Net income for the year advanced 2.9 percent to 378 million
rand from a year earlier, the company said on March 15.  To contact the reporter on this story:
